abstract: Orlando City SC and New York City FC, both new to Major League Soccer, have taken different approaches to building teams; Orlando favors stability with star midfielder Kaka, while NYCFC continues to change lineup as season progresses.
lead_paragraph: The two franchises, who joined Major League Soccer this year, have experienced much of the same excitement and handled many of the same obstacles in the past few months.

headline.main: Orlando City S.C. and New York City F.C. Take Different Paths in M.L.S.
headline.print_headline: Separate Ways for Two Teams New to M.L.S.
